<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[r 30.1] r 30.1 Damages under judgment (cf SCR Part 35, rule 1; DCR Part 11A, rule 2(2); LCR Part 10A, rule 2(2))">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-1" type="ext"/>[r 30.1]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Damages under judgment (cf SCR Part 35, rule 1; DCR Part 11A, rule 2(2); LCR Part 10A, rule 2(2))</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>30.1</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-1.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-1.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>This rule applies to proceedings in which judgment against a party has been given for damages to be assessed.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-1.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-1.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Subject to subrule (3), the proceedings are to proceed to trial for assessment of damages.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-1.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-1.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If the proceedings are carried on against the party on any claim for relief not determined by the judgment, or against any other party, the trial for assessment of damages is to be held together with any other trial in the proceedings.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTES"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT30.R1.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTES</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_UCPR.SGM_UCPN.UCPR.30-1-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[30.1.5] Enquiry as to damages"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.30-1-5" type="ext"/>[30.1.5] </edpnum><title>Enquiry as to damages</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The court should only refuse a party's request for an enquiry as to damages if there is no evidence of damage or it comes to the conclusion that the party cannot reasonably hope to obtain any damages or that the damages will only be nominal: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1890"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr007781" spanref="cr007781-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="LRNSWEQ"/><ci:volume num="11"/><ci:page num="231"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr007781" spanref="cr007781-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="258" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Griffin v Mercantile Bank</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007781-001" status="unval">(1890) 11 LR (NSW) Eq 231</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr007781-002" status="unval">at 258</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="68085" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1896"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr007782" spanref="cr007782-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="WNNSW"/><ci:volume num="12"/><ci:page num="131"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Union Bank v Downes</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007782-001" status="unval">(1896) 12 WN (NSW) 131</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="44250" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> and <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1982"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr007783" spanref="cr007783-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="BPR"/><ci:volume num="2"/><ci:page num="9640"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Enkelmann v Glissan</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007783-001" status="unval">(1982) 2 BPR 9640</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_UCPR.SGM_UCPN.UCPR.30-1-10" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[30.1.10] Separate hearing of liability and damages issues"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.30-1-10" type="ext"/>[30.1.10] </edpnum><title>Separate hearing of liability and damages issues</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The present rule presupposes that judgment was delivered in proceedings where the amount of damages was not in issue. If damages were also in issue in the proceedings, the rule does not confer a discretion to permit a supplementary hearing on damages issues that a party failed to substantiate: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr007784" spanref="cr007784-001"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC200905329"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Voss v Ipkendanz</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> [2009] NSWSC 562; <ci:span spanid="cr007784-001"> BC200905329</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="475523" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[r 30.2] r 30.2 Value of goods under judgment (cf SCR Part 35, rule 2) ">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-2" type="ext"/>[r 30.2]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Value of goods under judgment (cf SCR Part 35, rule 2) </title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>30.2</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Rule 30.1</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 applies to proceedings in which judgment is given for the value of goods to be assessed (with or without damages to be assessed) in the same way as it applies to a judgment for damages to be assessed.</text></p>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT30.R2.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_UCPR.SGM_UCPN.UCPR.30-2-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[30.2.5] Separate assessment"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.30-2-5" type="ext"/>[30.2.5] </edpnum><title>Separate assessment</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The value of the goods and damages for their detention must be separately assessed: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr007785" spanref="cr007785-001"><ci:reporter value="All ER"/><ci:volume num="2"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1963"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="314"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr007786" spanref="cr007786-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="WLR"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1963"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="644"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">General and Finance Facilities Ltd v Cooks Cars (Romford) Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007785-001">[1963] 2 All ER 314</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr007786-002" status="unval">[1963] 1 WLR 644</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>. </text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[r 30.3] r 30.3 Damages to time of assessment (cf SCR Part 35, rule 3; DCR Part 27, rule 2; LCR Part 22, rule 2)">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-3" type="ext"/>[r 30.3]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Damages to time of assessment (cf SCR Part 35, rule 3; DCR Part 27, rule 2; LCR Part 22, rule 2)</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>30.3</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-3.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-3.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If damages are to be assessed in respect of:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-3.1.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-3.1.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>a continuing cause of action, or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-3.1.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-3.1.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>repeated breaches of recurring obligations, or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-3.1.C"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-3.1.C" type="ext"/>(c)</lilabel>
<p><text>intermittent breaches of a continuing obligation, </text></p>
</li>
</l>
<p><text>the damages are to be assessed up to the time of assessment, including damages for breaches occurring after the commencement of the proceedings.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-3.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R30-3.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Subrule (1) applies to the assessment of damages under this Part or otherwise.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTES"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT30.R3.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTES</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_UCPR.SGM_UCPN.UCPR.30-3-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[30.3.5] Time for assessment"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.30-3-5" type="ext"/>[30.3.5] </edpnum><title>Time for assessment</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>If it were not for this rule, damages at common law would be assessed down to the date of the commencement of proceedings: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1701"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr007787" spanref="cr007787-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="MODREP"/><ci:volume num="12"/><ci:page num="542"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr007788" spanref="cr007788-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="ER"/><ci:volume num="88"/><ci:page num="1506"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Fitter v Veal</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007787-001" status="unval">(1701) 12 Mod Rep 542</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr007788-002" status="unval">88 ER 1506</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="96808" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> alias <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1701"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr007789" spanref="cr007789-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="SALK"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:page num="11"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Fetter v Beale</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007789-001" status="unval">(1701) 1 Salk 11</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>. Apart from this rule, it should be noted that equitable damages under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="OTH.CAIRUK" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">Lord Cairns' Act 1858 (UK)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 may be assessed in certain circumstances as at the time of assessment. The court may fix the date for assessment of damages as any date that may be appropriate in the circumstances: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr007790" spanref="cr007790-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1975"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="512"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">ASA Constructions Pty Ltd v Iwanov</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007790-001">[1975] 1 NSWLR 512</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr007791" spanref="cr007791-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="CH"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1974"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="30"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Wroth v Tyler</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007791-001" status="unval">[1974] Ch 30</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="36135" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> and <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr007792" spanref="cr007792-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1983"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="305"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Madden v Kevereski</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007792-001">[1983] 1 NSWLR 305</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>. </text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_UCPR.SGM_UCPN.UCPR.30-3-10" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[30.3.10] Continuing cause of action"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.30-3-10" type="ext"/>[30.3.10] </edpnum><title>Continuing cause of action</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>For there to be a continuing cause of action within this rule, there must be a continuance both in the breach and the obligation: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr007793" spanref="cr007793-001"><ci:reporter value="All ER"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1958"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="91"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr007794" spanref="cr007794-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="WLR"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1958"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="16"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">National Coal Board v Galley</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007793-001">[1958] 1 All ER 91</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr007794-002" status="unval">[1958] 1 WLR 16</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>. It is, however, well established that tortious conduct of particular kinds such as trespass or nuisance is within the expression: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr007795" spanref="cr007795-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="CH"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1894"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="293"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Hole v Chard Union</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007795-001" status="unval">[1894] 1 Ch 293</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr007796" spanref="cr007796-001"><ci:reporter value="VR"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1976"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="654"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Oldham v Lawson (No 1)</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007796-001">[1976] VR 654</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="32887" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>. See also <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1890"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr007797" spanref="cr007797-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="CHD"/><ci:volume num="43"/><ci:page num="607"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Jones v Simes</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007797-001" status="unval">(1890) 43 Ch D 607</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="57116" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr007798" spanref="cr007798-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="CH"/><ci:volume num="2"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1893"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="171"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr007798" spanref="cr007798-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="174" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Read v Wotton</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007798-001" status="unval">[1893] 2 Ch 171</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr007798-002" status="unval">at 174</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr007799" spanref="cr007799-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="AC"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1908"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="27"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">West Leigh Colliery Co Ltd v Tunnicliffe &amp; Hampson Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007799-001" status="unval">[1908] AC 27</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="130186" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr007800" spanref="cr007800-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="CH"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1920"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="57"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Wheeler v Keeble (1914) Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007800-001" status="unval">[1920] 1 Ch 57</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr007801" spanref="cr007801-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="CH"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1929"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="92"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr007801" spanref="cr007801-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="104" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Re Keystone Knitting Mills Trade Mark</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr007801-001" status="unval">[1929] 1 Ch 92</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr007801-002" status="unval">at 104</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>.</text></p>
</bodytext>
